<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-06T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-06T07:00:00-05:00" n="531" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.4016/2051: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-06T13:00:00+01:00">January 6, 1939—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 6—9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>13. Embassy’s telegrams 764, December 29, 1 p.m.<note n="41" xml:id="d531fn41"><ref target="frus1938v02#pg_418"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1938, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 418</ref>.</note> and 6,
                                January 3, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <p>The following third-person note, dated December 31, has been received
                                today from the Foreign Office.</p>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“In reply to <hi rend="italic">note verbale</hi> No. 274 of
                                    December 29, 1938,<note n="40" xml:id="d531fn40">Not
                                        printed.</note> the Foreign Office has the honor to inform
                                    the Embassy of the United States of America that the assurances
                                    given the Government of the United States in <hi rend="italic">note verbale</hi> Number 84–60 SHT. 14–12 of December 30,
                                    with regard to the examination and consideration of treaty
                                    rights to which American citizens are entitled, apply also to
                                    the present inquiry.”</p>
                            </quote>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>